cite.text: Krull, A., Buchholz, T.O. and Jug, F., 2019. "Noise2Void - Learning denoising from single noisy images". In Proceedings of the IEEE/CVF conference on computer vision and pattern recognition (pp. 2129-2137).

rdf_content.description: This model is a UNet trained with the Noise2Void algorithm to denoise images. The training data consists of images of non-uniformly clustered nuclei in the mouse skull. The notebook used to train this model is available on the CAREamics documentation website at the following link: https://careamics.github.io/0.1/applications/Noise2Void/Mouse_Nuclei/.
rdf_content.name: MouseNuclei_N2V
